Key Match Events: Detroit Pistons won the match against Toronto Raptors with a score of 99-95
Pre-Game Insights: The Pistons were missing Tim Hardaway Jr due to an injury, and Malik Beasley replaced him in the starting lineup
Post-Match Reflections: The Pistons remain unbeaten in NBA Cup play, advancing to 6-8 on the year
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cade Cunningham struggled with his shooting, hitting just six shots for 15 points, but still collected a double-double by dishing out ten assists
Others: Jaden Ivey returned to the lineup after taking a game off due to an injury
